description:
### HTML End Tag by Start Tag

The function htmlEndTagByStartTag takes a start tag as a string and returns the corresponding end tag. Note: The input does not contain any attributes.

Input: A string representing the start tag (`<tag>`, `<tag/>`, or `<tag />`).
Output: A string representing the end tag (`</tag>`).

Example:

``` htmlEndTagByStartTag("<button type='button' disabled>") // "</button>" ```

tests.input: <div id='my_area' class='data' title='This is a test for title on Div tag'>
